Adding a lesson

- Create a new lesson directory- for example lesson1
- Create a phrases.txt file inside the new lesson directory- for example lesson1/phrases.txt
- Inside the phrases.txt, put one english phrase per line
- Press Command Space and open Terminal
- Inside terminal type cd ~/Documents/website/shahinaba.github.io/
- run python3 gen_data.py lesson_name (for example lesson3)
- run python3 gen_html.py lesson_name (for example lesson3)
- Update index.html with a new link by adding a new line like <a href="lesson1.html"><h2>Lesson 1<h2></a>
- In Github Desktop, press commit in the bottom left, and Push origin at the top